You may not engage in Production Use of the Software unless you have entered into a separate written commercial agreement with EXOCHAIN (a “Commercial Agreement”). That Commercial Agreement will specify your rights to Production Use, applicable fees, support terms, and any royalties, including the royalty terms in Section 4 if applicable.

Absent a Commercial Agreement, all Production Use is prohibited.

4. Royalty for Covered Offerings (10% Gross Evergreen)
Certain Production Uses will be considered “Covered Offerings” and require a continuing royalty.

4.1 Covered Offering.
A “Covered Offering” is any product or service that:
 • (a) is offered, sold, licensed, or otherwise monetized by you or your affiliates; and
 • (b) uses the Software, or any substantial portion or modified version of it, as a material component of its functionality, especially for regulated-entity, governance, decision-record, or evidentiary workflows (including, without limitation, offerings built on or incorporating LegalDyne, decision.forum, CrossChecked, exoclaw, exoforge, hardshell, or EXOCHAIN-based rails).

4.2 Royalty.
Unless your Commercial Agreement explicitly states otherwise, for each Covered Offering you shall pay EXOCHAIN an ongoing royalty equal to ten percent (10%) of the gross revenue received by you and your affiliates from that Covered Offering, worldwide, for as long as that Covered Offering is offered or monetized (the “Royalty”).

4.3 Gross Revenue.
“Gross revenue” means the total amounts actually received by you or your affiliates from customers or third parties for the Covered Offering, before deductions of any kind, except for: (i) taxes separately stated and collected; and (ii) bona fide refunds and chargebacks.

4.4 Reporting and Payment.
Unless different terms are set in a Commercial Agreement:
 • You shall provide written royalty reports to EXOCHAIN at least quarterly, stating gross revenue for each Covered Offering and the corresponding Royalty due.
 • Royalties shall be paid within thirty (30) days after the end of each reporting period, in U.S. dollars, to the account designated by EXOCHAIN.
 • EXOCHAIN may, at its expense and on reasonable notice, audit your relevant records no more than once per year to verify Royalty calculations. If an audit reveals an underpayment of more than five percent (5%) for the audited period, you shall reimburse EXOCHAIN’s reasonable audit costs.

4.5 No Cap; Evergreen.
The Royalty is uncapped and remains payable for the full commercial life of each Covered Offering, unless otherwise agreed in a signed Commercial Agreement with EXOCHAIN.

